OL,3,CMurder jury hears man who admits
OL,4,Cfiring gun did not know weapon was
OL,5,Cloaded
OL,7,FHe said that the man had threatened to
OL,8,Fburn his house down and he "knew" that
OL,9,Fman would be inside the home of Mr
OL,10,FDawson that afternoon.
OL,12,FHe went to the property with his four
OL,13,Fco-accused where he told the court he
OL,14,Fonly intended to fire the gun into the
OL,15,Fhouse to frighten people inside, but
OL,16,FMr Dawson was killed "by accident".
OL,18,FReay described Mr Dawson as entirely
OL,19,Finnocent and that he has to live with
OL,20,Fthe guilt of accidentally killing him.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
