OL,3,CMurder jury hears man who admits
OL,4,Cfiring gun did not know weapon was
OL,5,Cloaded
OL,7,FUnder cross examination, Reay was
OL,8,Fasked if he had only planned to
OL,9,Ffrighten people that day, then why did
OL,10,Fhe use live ammunition when blanks
OL,11,Fwould have "done the job".
OL,13,FHe replied that he never intended to
OL,14,Fkill or hurt anybody in the house and
OL,15,Fthat he was unable to see inside
OL,16,Fclearly because he was wearing a
OL,17,Fbalaclava, the blinds were closed and
OL,18,Fthe sun was in his eyes.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/9
