OL,3,CMurder jury hears man who admits
OL,4,Cfiring gun did not know weapon was
OL,5,Cloaded
OL,7,FLawson, 38, of Frosterley Gardens, was
OL,8,Fcalled to give evidence and told the
OL,9,Fcourt that he had agreed to help his
OL,10,F"good pal" Reay frighten people inside
OL,11,Fthe house by "putting the windows
OL,12,Fthrough" but he had no idea that Reay
OL,13,Fhad brought a gun.
OL,15,FLawson was asked how his DNA was found
OL,16,Fon the bullet casings recovered from
OL,17,Fthe scene.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/9
